This paper discusses the convergence of backpropagation in deep architectures and the influence of network structure, activation type, denoising, and dropout rate on it. These topics are all related to machine learning and specifically deep learning, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), which are subfields of machine learning. The paper also discusses the use of neural networks (cs.NE) and the optimization of learning parameters (cs.AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, and cs.CL.
